<DOC><DOCNO> AP891113-0135 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-11-13-89 2028EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-Brazil-Hostages     11-13 0145</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Brazil-Hostages,0149</SECOND><HEAD>Prisoners Take 40 Hostages in Southern Brazil</HEAD><DATELINE>RIO DE JANEIRO, Brazil (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Eight inmates wielding iron clubsand revolvers seized 40 hostages at a prison cafeteria in southernBrazil, a state official said Monday.   Negotiations were being conducted with the prisoners and 300heavily armed policeman had cordoned off the building, said RubensBuelo, a justice official in Curitiba, capital of Parana state, 525miles southwest of Rio.   Buelo said the hostages, all employees of the Central Prison ofParana, include the director, deputy director and several staffpsychologists. He said the 40 were taken hostage in the cafeteriaduring the lunch hour.   The prisoners were demanding more weapons and an armored car fora getaway, Buelo said.   ``We're sure negotiations will be successful,'' Buelo said.``We're doing our best to keep everyone calm and confort thefamilies of the hostages.''</TEXT></DOC>